content:
Check:
  all:
    - name: --DTHREL
      operator: non_empty
    - name: --DTHREL
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: Y
    - name: --DTHREL
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: U
    - name: --DTHREL
      operator: not_equal_to
      value: N
Core:
  Id: CDISC.SENDIG.183
  Version: '1'
  Status: Draft
Description: Raise an error when record is --DTHREL is not null and is not equal to
  'Y', 'N' or 'U'
Outcome:
  Message: --DTHREF must be 'Y, 'N', 'U' or null.
Rule Type: Record Data
Sensitivity: Record
Authorities:
  - Organization: CDISC
    Standards:
      - Name: SENDIG
        Version: '3.1'
        References:
          - Origin: SDTM and SENDIG Conformance Rules
            Rule Identifier:
              Id: '183'
              Version: '1'
            Version: '2.0'
            Citations:
              - Cited Guidance: --DTHREL Describes the relationship of a particular
                  finding to the death of a subject (Y=caused death, N=did not cause
                  death, U=unknown). May be left null if not available.
                Document: SENDIG v3.1
                Section: Section 6.3.7-6.3.8
Scope:
  Classes:
    Include:
      - FINDINGS
  Domains:
    Include:
      - MA
      - MI
